that rite of spring in which the TV networks go to great lengths to
goose ratings because this is the period in which advertising rates
are set _ even though the networks and advertisers know the
programming bears scant resemblance to anything else that will
appear all year. No wonder broadcasting and advertising executives
are starting to question the whole tradition. By Bill Carter.
