<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Play ball!
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ It is the season for home runs, fastballs and
strikeouts. The Atlanta Braves welcome kids into the team's virtual
clubhouse at www.atlantabraves.com (click on Kids Korner in the Fan
Clubhouse square). You'll find games, facts and special events.
True fans will want to keep this site handy for updates throughout
the season.
</P>
<P>
   RIDDLE ME THIS!
</P>
<P>
   Silly kitty! Riddles are for kids _ especially the ones in a new
book by Katy Hall and Lisa Eisenberg called ``Kitty Riddles'' (Dial
Books for Young Readers, $13). Here are some of our favorites from
the book: Q: What's little and soft and says, ``Beow!'' ``Beow!''
A: A kitty with a cold! Q: Where do kitties find out what's
happening? A: From the Daily Mews! Q: How should you pet an angry,
wet kitty? A: From fur, fur away! Make up some riddles of your own
and send them to nfk(at)ajc.com. We'll run them in the paper if
they crack us up!
</P>
<P>
   SEARCH THE WORLD FOR DINOSAUR EGGS
</P>
<P>
   Easter may be over, but you still can hunt for eggs _ dinosaur
eggs! National Geographic's site at www.nationalgeographic.
com/dinoeggs/intro.html tells about the international hunt for
dinosaur nests. And you get to look inside the eggs of dinosaurs
and meet scientists who study the eggs. Stay tuned for much more
dinosaur information in NFK!
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
