<DOCNO> NYT20000424.0085 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-24 10:41 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5410 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-ORGANIZERS0425-COX     04-24 0395
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ORGANIZERS0425-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Palm Pilots can get you there
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Hand-held organizers have always been able to
manage your to-do lists so you aren't late for important
appointments, and they can store phone numbers so you can call
ahead even if you are running late.
</P>
<P>
   Now they can also help you find your way to that appointment
just about anywhere in North America.
</P>
<P>
   Rand McNally, the map people, have developed a mapping and
global positioning system (GPS) device designed to work with the
Palm III and Palm V organizers.
</P>
<P>
   StreetFinder Deluxe 2000 comes with a GPS antenna that plugs
directly into the back of the organizer. As you travel, the antenna
calculates your exact position by correlating signals from a
network of orbiting satellites and displays your position on a map
on the screen of the organizer.
</P>
<P>
   If you program the system with the route you want to follow, it
displays text messages telling you when and in which direction to
turn to reach your destination.
</P>
<P>
   To program the Palm organizer with the maps and directions you
need, you have to link the organizer to your personal computer.
</P>
<P>
   StreetFinder Deluxe 2000 comes with StreetFinder CD-ROM software
that lets you access maps and directions through your home
computer. Using the software, you can look up specific addresses
for office buildings, restaurants, hotels and other services along
your travel route anywhere in the United States, Canada and most of
Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Once you've compiled your travel information on the personal
computer, you can download it to your organizer and attach it to
the GPS antenna inside your car. The system also comes with a
bracket for attaching the unit to the windshield, plus rechargeable
batteries, a cigarette lighter power supply plug and an AC adapter.
</P>
<P>
   The StreetFinder Deluxe 2000 for the Palm III can be ordered
online from Rand McNally's Web site at www.randmcnally.com for
$179. It is also available from Rand McNally map stores, but the
company has no stores in Ohio, Kentucky or Indiana.
</P>
<P>
   The StreetFinder Deluxe 2000 for the Palm V can also be ordered
online, but Rand McNally said that version of the product won't be
shipped until the middle of May. It sells for $199.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
