<HEADLINE>
ON VIDEO, `FIGHT CLUB' IS STILL A MESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Fight Club'' _ Almost any actor can look good
with a solid script and a decent director. This mess of a movie
features neither. And Edward Norton, as a down-and-outer, is still
great. Criticized for its violence on all sides, that's not the
problem. Director David Fincher is so sophomorically aware of his
testosterone metaphor _ boxing as a symbol of male nuttiness _ that
he transforms what might have been watchable into a pretentious
preliminary bout. It's for anyone who believes that a shaky camera
and a shakier sense of drama is a formula for art.
</P>
<P>
   ``End of Days'' _ This must have sounded better at the pitch
meeting than it plays on the screen. Arnold must save the world
from the Devil. Schwarzenegger vs. Satan. While Gabriel Byrne's
turn as the arch fiend is terrific, at the end of these days, there
are no surprises.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mumford'' _ Lawrence Kasdan's best film in years is an
affectionate sendup of small-town paranoia and psychiatry. While
Loren Dean carries the picture as the shrink wrapped up in his
clients' lives, citizens Hope Davis, Alfre Woodard, and David
Paymer steal the picture.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 2: ``Being John Malkovich,'' ``Anywhere
But Here,'' ``Galaxy Quest'' (DVD), ``Dogma.'' May 9: ``American
Beauty,'' ``The Hollywood Knights,'' ``Bringing Out the Dead.'' May
16: ``The World Is Not Enough'' (DVD), ``Dreaming of Joseph Lees,''
``Felicia's Journey,'' ``The End of the Affair.'' May 23: ``Sleepy
Hollow,'' ``Escape From Mars,'' ``Train of Life.'' May 30: ``Snow
Falling on Cedars'' (DVD), ``Miss Julie,'' ``Man on the Moon''
(DVD).'' June 6: ``Girl, Interrupted'' (DVD), ``Mr. Death'' (DVD),
``Backlash,'' ``Kiss the Sky'' (DVD), ``A Scandal in Paris,'' ``On
Our Merry Way'' (DVD), ``Andy Kaufman Plays Carnegie Hall.'' June
13: ``Leila'' (DVD), ``The Emperor and the Assassin'' (DVD), ``The
Third Miracle'' (DVD), ``Light It Up.''
</P>
