   CLINTON-POLITICS (Undated) _ Bill Clinton attends lunch for
Representative Mike Forbes, the former Republican who is now a
Democrat. He is just one of many Members of Congress who voted to
impeach or remove the president, who finds himself greeted nowadays
with a warm White House embrace. Although after the votes Clinton
vowed revenge for those who tried to oust him, he is now treating
it like any other political defeat. Other examples: DeLay is the
chief vote counter on China trade, Rogan was invited to White House
meeting on gun control, Hyde is also working with Clinton on gun
control. By Marc Lacey.
