<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) - The saga of little Elian Gonzalez is
heart-rending human drama, but it is easy to lose sight of the
central issue here because of the many political and emotional
distractions. The irresponsible Miami relatives had no legal right
to custody of Elian. This is not about Castro, or communism, or
President Clinton or the timing of the armed raid. It is about
family values and parental authority, reuniting a separated father
and son. By MARIANNE MEANS . (Already filed.)
