<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKN-WILKENS _ ATLANTA _ Lenny Wilkens, the NBA's winningest
coach, resigns after the worst season in his 27 years.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BKN-BRADLEY-WILKENS _ Mark Bradley tells us who he thinks should
be the next coach of the Hawks. (Bradley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKN-MOORE-WILKENS _ Terence Moore writes about the resignation
of Lenny Wilkens (Moore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HEAT _ MIAMI _ Double or nothing. That's the proposition
facing the Miami Heat as they prepare for Tuesday's rematch against
the Detroit Pistons. Each of the past two seasons, the Heat won
only one of the opening two games at home, then dropped both series
to the Knicks. (Skolnick, Palm Beach Post). MOVED.BKN-WNBA-DRAFT _
The WNBA draft is today. Texas star Edwina Brown is expected to be
drafted. (Halliburton, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
