<P>
   CUBA-ELIAN _WASHINGTON _House Speaker J. Dennis Hastert Monday
condemned the ``excessive force'' used in last weekend's pre-dawn
raid on the home of Elian Gonzalez's Miami relatives and called
upon the House Judiciary Committee chairman to hold hearings into
the incident. But they could be wading into dangerous political
waters. The little boy and his father, meanwhile, could be moved to
the Wye River Plantation on Maryland's eastern shore Monday, as
attorney Gregory Craig joins the federal government in their
appeals court defense. Developing.
</P>
<P>
   (Lipman, Cox News Service)
