<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; BIOSCOPE (COLUMN) _  &LR; Congress will enter one of biotechnology's
ethical minefields this week, when a Senate committee considers
whether the government should fund stem cell research. Stem cells
produce other types of specialized cells. The human embryo contains
the most potent stem cells. They can make every nerve, bone and
fiber in you or me.  &UR; COLUMN BY TOM ABATE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; ORPHANAGE _  &LR; After years of watching their names roll by in the
credits of films like ``Jurassic Park'' and ``Star Wars: Episode I
_ The Phantom Menace,'' Scott Stewart, Stuart Maschwitz and
Jonathan Rothbart last year left Industrial Light and Magic, George
Lucas' special-effects powerhouse, to form the Orphanage.
 &UR; BY KELLY ZITO &LR;
</P>
