<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TIMES-MEETING-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIMES CO. RESCHEDULES ANNUAL MEETING 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The New York Times Co. has rescheduled its annual
meeting for May 23. The meeting had been scheduled for this
Thursday but was postponed because of a delay in processing the
company's proxy statement by the Securities and Exchange
Commission.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the routine business, the company is asking
shareholders to authorize a new class of stock to represent New
York Times Digital, the company's Internet business division.
</P>
<P>
   In January, the Times Co. filed an initial registration
statement with the SEC for the new class of shares related to the
Internet unit. The shareholder vote paves the way for the offering
but does not require the company to proceed, said Catherine Mathis,
a company spokeswoman. After the annual meeting, the company will
decide whether and when to offer the shares ``based on market
conditions,'' she said. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
