<SLUG> BC-CUBAN-BOY-TEXT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEXT OF FINAL OFFER FOR DEAL ON MOVING BOY 
</HEADLINE>
  (With CUBAN-BOY-FORCE) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Following are excerpts from the final proposal from Attorney
General Janet Reno and the Justice Department to the Miami civic
leaders they were negotiating with for the reunion of Elian
Gonzalez with his father, as provided by the civic leaders:
</P>
<P>
   1. By 2:30 a.m. on Saturday, April 22, Elian Gonzalez will be
delivered to the Miami Federal Courthouse accompanied by Lazaro
Gonzalez's family members, where he will be in the A.G.'s custody
and guarded by U.S. marshals. The group will be driven to a hotel
for overnight accommodations. They will be guarded by U.S. marshals
and may not leave with Elian.
</P>
<P>
   2. On Saturday, April 22, Elian Gonzalez and Lazaro Gonzalez's
family will drive or fly to Washington, D.C., under escort by
U.S.M.S. and proceed to Airlie House. The child will be guarded by
U.S.M.S.
</P>
<P>
   3. Upon Juan Gonzalez's arrival at Airlie House, A.G. will
parcel Elian Gonzalez into Juan Miguel Gonzalez's care. During the
residence at Airlie, Elian Gonzalez will live with Juan Miguel
Gonzalez. Lazaro Gonzalez's family will reside at Airlie House in
separate quarters.
</P>
<P>
   4. A.G. to choose three recognized experts.
</P>
<P>
   5. The attorney general wants to ensure a smooth transition for
Elian Gonzalez from the Miami relatives to his father. To that end,
parole will be conditioned on Juan Miguel Gonzalez's agreement to
meet with members of the Lazaro Gonzalez family to meet with the
government experts, and to give those experts access to Elian
Gonzalez for appropriate evaluation. The experts shall advise the
attorney general as to what further transitional arrangements may
be appropriate.
</P>
<P>
   6. The attorney general, as a condition of parole, shall direct
and appropriate transition in consultation with the government
experts, not to exceed one week.
</P>
<P>
   7. The parties will remain in residence for a period determined
by the A.G., not to exceed one week.
</P>
<P>
   8. Departure control order to be issued for Elian Gonzalez ...
to assure Elian Gonzalez remains in the United States consistent
with existing (United States Court of Appeals for the 11th Circuit)
injunction.
</P>
<P>
   9. Lazaro Gonzalez and his family agree to waive any right to
sue Juan Gonzalez and his family with respect to the custody of
Elian Gonzalez.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
